name: BostonGlobe
text: Holyoke Mayor Alex Morse, who lost his challenge against incumbent Representative Richard Neal, is speaking now. https://t.co/vNZkwqr5TQ

name: BostonGlobe
text: Representative Joe Kennedy III, who has conceded the Democratic nomination for US Senate to incumbent Senator Ed Markey, is speaking now. https://t.co/7NWdcF2OnK

name: BostonGlobe
text:
"Obviously, these results were not the ones we were hoping for. But to everyone who fought with us... I am so proud of what we accomplished. What we built together," Kennedy says. 
Watch live: https://t.co/YfZMb62Oy4

name: BostonGlobe
text: Senator Ed Markey, who won the Democratic primary for Senate Tuesday after fending off a challenge from a much younger Representative Joseph P. Kennedy III, is expected to speak shortly. https://t.co/0tCprENy3U

name: BostonGlobe
text: "To my family, the Kennedy family -- whose name was invoked far more often than I anticipated in this race -- to my mom, my dad, my twin brother, and the rest of a rowdy bunch of crazy cousins: You all are my heroes," Kennedy says. https://t.co/AfbTySrYcp

name: BostonGlobe
text:
With just over 50 percent reporting, Jesse Mermell holds a slight lead in the US House District four Democratic primary with 24.9 percent; Jake Auchincloss follows with 22.3 percent, and Becky Grossman holds 16.9 percent of the vote. 
Live results: https://t.co/iFXMzvtPQu https://t.co/OlS5jMxF7V

name: BostonGlobe
text: Senator Edward Markey, who won the Democratic primary for Senate Tuesday after fending off a challenge from Representative Joseph P. Kennedy III, is speaking now. https://t.co/v95ISHWWGT

name: BostonGlobe
text:
"Today and every day we say, 'Black lives matter. Black voices matter,'" Markey says. 
Watch live: https://t.co/Y1OAWeLBSq

name: BostonGlobe
text: Markey touts "environmental justice" in speech: "That's the Green New Deal. The one issue: combating the climate crisis which defines our future. Every other problem is linked to it. No solutions to any challenge will be successful unless we address it." https://t.co/Kv7rfupAZC

name: BostonGlobe
text: "This is a matter of life and death. The very future of our civilization depends upon it. There is no time for simply doing what we can. There is no time for compromise. . . We must pass a Green New Deal," Markey says. https://t.co/PLlerogqRx

name: BostonGlobe
text: "Now is our moment to think big, to build big, to be big. This is what this election is all about. This is what this moment demands," Markey says, touting his "unapologetically progressive stances" on key issues. https://t.co/yHkAd4jDi6
